 [Text(0, 0, 'Non-Defaulter(0)'), Text(1, 0, 'Defaulter(1)')])

The target values in this dataset represent whether a client has payment difficulties or not. This is critical because: Target value = 1: The client has experienced payment difficulties (e.g., late payments). This is a high-risk client. Target value = 0: The client has no payment difficulties, making them a low-risk client. By analyzing the distribution of these values, the bank can identify patterns or features associated with defaults.
